modules.description: Provides functions for reading from and writing to C-like structures using Bigarray, enabling direct memory manipulation. Works with byte sequences and structured data layouts similar to C's struct type. Used for low-level data parsing and serialization in network protocols and binary file formats.

Provides asynchronous read and write operations on Cstruct buffers using Lwt, with support for socket communication. It handles file descriptors and socket addresses, enabling non-blocking data transfer. Specific functions include filling buffers from file descriptors, sending data over sockets, and receiving data with address information.
